<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="392" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1546,2003]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1546,1571]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species, previously classified as 
<taxonomicName box="[700,863,1546,1571]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubilio">
<emphasis box="[700,863,1546,1571]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Rutilus rubilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, cannot be placed in the genus 
<emphasis box="[1221,1307,1546,1571]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">
<taxonomicName box="[1221,1303,1546,1571]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rutilus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
because of the pharyngeal teeth formulae, 
<number box="[519,533,1582,1607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" value="5.0">5</number>
- 
<quantity box="[542,590,1582,1607]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[601,713,1582,1607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubilio">
<emphasis box="[601,713,1582,1607]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">R. rubilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<number box="[777,792,1582,1607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" value="6.0">6</number>
- 
<number box="[800,815,1582,1607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" value="6.0">6</number>
or 
<number box="[861,876,1582,1607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" value="6.0">6</number>
- 
<quantity box="[885,932,1582,1607]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[944,1023,1582,1607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[944,1023,1582,1607]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Rutilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of the small size and the riverine preference as opposed to still waters and large size in 
<taxonomicName box="[750,829,1618,1643]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[750,829,1618,1643]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Rutilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Similarly, it cannot be placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1317,1396,1620,1643]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Leucos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1317,1396,1620,1643]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Leucos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the presence of prominent tubercles at the center of each scale of the body and on the head in reproductive males (
<figureCitation box="[159,230,1690,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1357,1378]" captionTargetBox="[202,1434,515,1328]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[150,1436,483,1335]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 4. Anterior part of body of male Sarmarutilus rubilio showing prominent tubercles at centers of scales (from Bianco &amp; Taraborelli, 1985)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225782/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,230,1691,1715]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
), a character unknown in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[656,735,1692,1715]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Leucos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[656,735,1692,1715]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Leucos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and for the preferentially riverine habits as opposed to still waters in the five species of 
<taxonomicName box="[483,562,1728,1751]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Leucos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[483,562,1728,1751]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Leucos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, it shows a marked lateral stripe, quite different from that of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Leucos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">L. aula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, masked by heavy pigmentation on flanks formed by well marked crescent triangular spot on scales (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1405,1762,1787]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1514,1536]" captionTargetBox="[173,1424,552,1475]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,519,1492]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Native species of the Rutilus complex in southern Mediterranean Europe: A) Leucos aula, 115 mm SL, R. Bacchiglione, northern Italy, April 1996 (IZA 0425); B) Leucos basak, 95 mm SL, Lake Ohrid, FYROM, August 1987, (IZA 0429); C) Leucos ylikiensis, 120 mm SL, Lake Yliki, April 1987 (IZA 8733); D) Leucos panosi, 130 mm SL, canal to Lake Trichonis, May 1987 (IZA 8766); E) Leucos albus, 98 mm SL, River Moraca, Montenegro, November 1999 (IZA 0421); F) Sarmarutilus rubilio, 100 mm SL, River Ofanto, southern Italy, February 2002 (IZA 02183); G) Rutilus pigus, 230 mm SL, Lake Major, northern Italy, (IZA 0474); H) Holotype of Rutilus stoumboudae new species, 148 mm SL, October 1998, Lake Volvi, Greece (IZA 02107)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225780/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">
Fig. 
<number box="[1390,1405,1763,1787]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
F), of a shape not found in any of all other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[749,828,1800,1823]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Leucos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[749,828,1800,1823]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Leucos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[889,968,1798,1823]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[889,968,1798,1823]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Rutilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the examined area. Finally, it is well separated from the 
<taxonomicName box="[369,448,1836,1859]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Leucos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[369,448,1836,1859]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Leucos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species on karyology grounds (Bianco 
<emphasis box="[896,946,1834,1859]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number box="[968,1026,1835,1859]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" value="2004.0">2004</number>
) and from 
<taxonomicName box="[1151,1230,1834,1859]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1151,1230,1834,1859]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Rutilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1286,1365,1836,1859]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Leucos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1286,1365,1836,1859]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Leucos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the mtDNA level (Ketmaier 
<emphasis box="[430,488,1870,1895]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">at al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[501,562,1871,1895]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" value="2008.0">2008</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="393" pageId="13" pageNumber="392" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1546,2003]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1906,1931]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Etymology</emphasis>
. The generic name derives from the Sarmatic Sea, or Lago Mare, an ancient central European inner freshwater sea where this monotypic genus probably has its evolutionary roots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1546,2003]" lastBlockId="14.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="393" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,296,1978,2003]" pageId="13" pageNumber="392">Origins.</emphasis>
Sequence variation of the entire mitochondrial cytochrome b gene shows a strict relationship among five species, which diverged from a 
<taxonomicName box="[556,689,151,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Leuciscinae">Leuciscinae</taxonomicName>
ancestor about 
<number box="[865,907,151,176]" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
million years ago, during the Lago Mare phase of the Mediterranean Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Bianco" box="[452,608,188,213]" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" refString="Bianco, P. G. (1990) Potential role of the palaeohistory of the Mediterranean and Parathetys basin on the early dispersal of Europe-Mediterranean freshwater fishes. Ichthyological Exploration of Freshwaters, 1, 167 - 184." type="journal article" year="1990">
Bianco, 
<number box="[548,608,188,212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Similar biogeographic and temporal patterns have been observed in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[224,309,223,248]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Telestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[224,309,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="393">Telestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which occupies the same geographic area (
<bibRefCitation author="Ketmaier" box="[807,1053,223,248]" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" refString="Ketmaier, V., Bianco, P. G., Krivokapic, M., Cobolli, M. &amp; De Matthaeis, E. (2004) Molecular phylogeny of two lineages of Leuciscinae cyprinids (Telestes and Scardinius) from the peri-Mediterranean area based on cytochrome b data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 32, 1061 - 1071. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2004.04.008" type="journal article" year="2004">
Ketmaier 
<emphasis box="[921,977,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="393">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[992,1053,224,248]" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). According to karyology (Bianco 
<emphasis box="[151,208,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="393">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[223,281,260,284]" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" value="2004.0">2004</number>
) 
<taxonomicName box="[296,527,260,285]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Sarmarutilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubilio">
<emphasis box="[296,527,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="393">Sarmarutilus rubilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
displays few, if any, elements with centromeric heterochromatin and many with solid telomeric bands; this evidence differentiates 
<taxonomicName box="[724,829,295,320]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Sarmarutilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubilio">
<emphasis box="[724,829,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="393">S. rubilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from two representative species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1356,1436,297,320]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Leucos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1356,1436,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="393">Leucos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[160,241,332,357]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Leucos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aula">
<emphasis box="[160,241,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="393">L. aula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[298,404,333,356]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Leucos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="panosi">
<emphasis box="[298,404,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="393">L. panosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The three examined species should be considered as of distinct origins and, according to molecular data, probably separated since the Lago Mare Phase of the Mediterranean Sea in the Miocene Messinian (
<number box="[160,174,404,429]" pageId="14" pageNumber="393" value="5.0">5</number>
MYA).
</paragraph>
